    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fabric formed in a satin weave usually from silk or a manufactured fiber. It has a lustrous face and dull, crepe back. Charmeuse is most often used for lingerie, evening dresses, blouses, and linings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
